# Flyway — pre-production schema changes

**Issues is not in production yet** ([AGENTS.md](../../AGENTS.md)). There are no deployed databases to migrate incrementally.

## Rule

| Situation | Action |
|-----------|--------|
| New/changed table or column | **Edit** [`V1.0.0__Database_Creation.sql`](../../src/main/resources/db/migration/V1.0.0__Database_Creation.sql) |
| Pre-production (now) | **Do not** add `V1.0.1__…`, `V1.1__…`, or other versioned migration files |
| After first production deploy | Switch to incremental Flyway versions; do not rewrite shipped migrations |

## Same PR checklist

1. Update `V1.0.0__Database_Creation.sql` (CREATE/ALTER in baseline script).
2. Update [`dev-import.sql`](../../src/main/resources/dev-import.sql) if seed data needs new NOT NULL columns or FKs — see [dev-import-sql-safety.mdc](dev-import-sql-safety.mdc).
3. Update JPA entities to match.
4. Run `mvn test` (Flyway runs on `@QuarkusTest` startup).

## Examples

```sql
-- ✅ Pre-production: add column to CREATE TABLE in V1.0.0
CREATE TABLE tb_projects (
    ...
    ticket_template_enabled BOOLEAN NOT NULL DEFAULT FALSE,
    ...
);

-- ❌ Pre-production: separate migration file
-- V1.0.1__Add_Ticket_Template.sql
ALTER TABLE tb_projects ADD COLUMN ...
```

## Never

- Bypass Flyway — schema still lives under `src/main/resources/db/migration/`.
- Add a new migration version while the project remains pre-production (unless the user explicitly requests production rollout prep).
